recalls.Component: SERVICE BRAKES, HYDRAULIC:BRAKE FLUID LOW WARNING: LAMP
recalls.Summary: THE INSTRUMENT PANEL BRAKE WARNING LIGHT WILL NOT ILLUMINATE WHEN THE BRAKE FLUID LEVEL IN THE MASTER CYLINDER DROPS SUFFICIENTLY TO ACTIVATE THE LOW LEVEL SWITCH DUE TO AN IMPROPERLY WIRED DIODE, REQUIRED BY FMVSS NO. 105, "HYDRAULIC BRAKE SYSTEMS."
recalls.Consequence: CONSEQUENCE OF NON-COMPLIANCE:  THERE WOULD BE NO INDICATION TO THE DRIVER OF THE VEHICLE THAT BRAKE FLUID WAS LOW.  LOW BRAKE FLUID CAN BE CAUSED BY A LEAK IN THE SYSTEM WHICH MAY RESULT IN PARTIAL OR COMPLETE LOSS OF BRAKES AND AN ACCIDENT.
recalls.Remedy: DEALERS WILL CORRECT THE ELECTRICAL CIRCUIT FOR THE BRAKE WARNING SYSTEM SO THAT THE WARNING LAMP WILL ILLUMINATE WHEN THE LOW LEVEL SWITCH IS ACTIVATED.
recalls.Notes: SYSTEM: BRAKES; HYDRAULIC; LAMP LIGHT; BRAKE WARNING; FMVSS 105.  VEHICLE DESCRIPTION: PASSENGER CARS.  NOTE: IF YOUR VEHICLE IS PRESENTED TO AN AUTHORIZED DEALER ON AN AGREED UPON SERVICE DATE AND THE REMEDY IS NOT PROVIDED WITHIN A REASONABLE TIME AND FREE OF CHARGE, OR THE REMEDY DOES NOT CORRECT THE DEFECT OR NONCOMPLIANCE, PLEASE CONTACT NISSAN SERVICE CENTER AT 1-800-647-7261. ALSO, CONTACT THE NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION'S AUTO SAFETY HOTLINE AT 1-800-424-9393.

THE GAS TANK ON THE 1995-1998 NISSAN 240SX IS MADE OF A COMPOSITE MATERIAL. BETWEEN FRIDAY MAY 7, AND SATURDAY MAY 8, 2010 A STRESS FRACTURE IN THE FUEL TANK FORMED ON THE PASSENGER SIDE OF THE VEHICLE, ADJACENT TO THE STRAP WHICH HOLDS THE TANK TO THE CAR. THE FRACTURE IN THE TANK RESULTED IN A LARGE QUANTITY OF FUEL LEAKING OVER THE GARAGE FLOOR. THIS WAS A VERY SERIOUS PROBLEM AS IT COULD HAVE LED TO A SEVERE VEHICLE AND HOUSE FIRE. THE FAILURE HAS NOT YET BEEN CORRECTED. TO PREVENT MORE FUEL FROM LEAKING FROM THE VEHICLE, AND TO REDUCE THE POSSIBILITY OF A FIRE, THE VEHICLE'S BATTERY WAS DISCONNECTED, AND THE REMAINING FUEL IN THE VEHICLE WAS SIPHONED INTO GASOLINE CONTAINER. THE REPLACEMENT OF THE TANK REQUIRES REMOVING THE ENTIRE REAR SUBFRAME OF THE VEHICLE WHICH CONSISTS OF THE REAR SUSPENSION AND DRIVELINE-- A LABOR INTENSIVE PROCESS.    THIS IS THE SECOND COMPOSITE PART THAT HAS FAILED ON THE VEHICLE WITHIN TWO MONTHS. THE MANUFACTURER ALSO USES A RADIATOR WITH COMPOSITE INLETS AND OUTLETS. OVER TIME AND DUE TO HEAT CYCLING, THE COMPOSITE MATERIAL DEVELOPED A STRESS FRACTURE RESULTING IN COOLANT BEING DUMPED OUT OF THE VEHICLE. *TR

issues.title: Engine Knock Sensor Failure
issues.description: The KA24DE engine's knock sensor commonly fails, causing engine knock, reduced performance, and potential engine damage if not addressed. The sensor is located under the intake manifold making replacement labor-intensive.
issues.fix_description: Replace knock sensor and wiring harness. Requires removing intake manifold for access.
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel and maintain proper engine timing. Regular maintenance can help extend sensor life.

issues.title: Power Window Motor Failure
issues.description: Window regulator motors frequently fail, particularly on the driver's side. The motors burn out due to age and wear, leaving windows stuck in position.
issues.fix_description: Replace window motor and potentially the regulator assembly. Remove door panel to access components.
issues.prevention: Lubricate window tracks regularly and avoid forcing windows that are slow to operate.

issues.title: Distributor Cap and Rotor Deterioration
issues.description: The distributor cap and rotor are prone to cracking and carbon tracking, causing misfires and poor engine performance. Common issue with the KA24DE engine's ignition system.
issues.fix_description: Replace distributor cap, rotor, and spark plug wires. Check timing and adjust if necessary.
issues.prevention: Replace cap and rotor every 30,000-40,000 miles as part of regular maintenance.

issues.title: Rear Subframe Bushing Wear
issues.description: Rear subframe bushings deteriorate over time, causing handling issues and tire wear. The rubber bushings crack and separate, allowing excessive movement in the rear suspension.
issues.fix_description: Replace all rear subframe bushings. May require special tools or press for installation.
issues.prevention: Regular inspections and avoiding harsh driving conditions can extend bushing life.

issues.title: Mass Air Flow Sensor Contamination
issues.description: The MAF sensor becomes contaminated with oil and debris, causing incorrect air flow readings and poor engine performance. Common on high-mileage vehicles.
issues.fix_description: Clean MAF sensor with appropriate cleaner or replace if damaged. Check air filter and intake system for oil contamination.
issues.prevention: Replace air filter regularly and fix any oil leaks in the engine or PCV system.

issues.title: Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: In-tank fuel pump commonly fails, especially in higher mileage vehicles. The pump motor burns out or the fuel pump sock becomes clogged, causing fuel starvation.
symptoms: loss of power at highway speeds
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump assembly including pump, sock filter, and sending unit. Requires dropping fuel tank.
issues.prevention: Keep fuel tank at least 1/4 full and replace fuel filter regularly to prevent pump damage.

issues.title: Radiator Cracking
issues.description: Plastic radiator tanks crack due to age and heat cycling, causing coolant leaks. The plastic becomes brittle and fails at the tank-to-core connection points.
issues.fix_description: Replace radiator with new unit. Flush cooling system and replace thermostat while performing repair.
issues.prevention: Regular coolant changes and avoiding overheating can extend radiator life.

issues.title: Door Handle Linkage Failure
issues.description: Interior and exterior door handle linkages break, preventing doors from opening. The plastic linkage rods become brittle and snap under normal use.
issues.fix_description: Replace broken linkage rods and clips. Remove door panel to access mechanism.
issues.prevention: Gentle use of door handles and regular lubrication of door mechanisms.

issues.title: Clutch Master Cylinder Failure
issues.description: The clutch master cylinder seals fail, causing clutch pedal to go to the floor and inability to shift gears. Internal seals deteriorate over time.
issues.fix_description: Replace clutch master cylinder and slave cylinder. Bleed clutch hydraulic system thoroughly.
issues.prevention: Regular clutch fluid changes and avoiding riding the clutch pedal.

issues.title: Timing Chain Tensioner Wear
issues.description: The timing chain tensioner wears out, causing timing chain slack and potential timing issues. Can lead to engine damage if chain jumps timing.
issues.fix_description: Replace timing chain tensioner, guides, and chain if stretched. Requires removing timing cover.
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with quality oil and avoiding high RPM when engine is cold.

issues.title: Exhaust Manifold Cracking
issues.description: Cast iron exhaust manifold develops cracks due to heat cycling, causing exhaust leaks and potential emissions issues. Common failure point on KA24DE engines.
issues.fix_description: Replace exhaust manifold with new or refurbished unit. Replace manifold gaskets and hardware.
issues.prevention: Allow engine to warm up properly and cool down gradually to minimize thermal stress.

issues.title: Speedometer Gear Failure
issues.description: Speedometer drive gear in the transmission fails, causing inaccurate or non-functioning speedometer. Plastic gear strips or breaks.
issues.fix_description: Replace speedometer drive gear and housing seal. Access through transmission side cover.
issues.prevention: Gentle driving and avoiding sudden acceleration can help prevent gear damage.

editorial.tagline: The drift king's affordable canvas awaits your vision
editorial.hero_blurb: The S14 240SX represents the sweet spot of Nissan's rear-wheel-drive sports car evolution. With its refined chassis dynamics and torquey KA24DE engine, it's the platform that launched a thousand drift builds.
editorial.essence: The S14 perfected the 240SX formula with improved rigidity, better weight distribution, and a more sophisticated suspension setup. It's the thinking enthusiast's choicerefined enough for daily driving yet capable enough for serious modification.
editorial.heritage: The second-generation 240SX built upon the S13's foundation with a more mature approach to sports car design. Nissan refined the chassis, improved the interior, and created what many consider the most balanced iteration of their iconic rear-wheel-drive platform.
editorial.design_philosophy: Nissan prioritized driving dynamics over outright power, creating a well-balanced chassis that could handle more power than the stock engine provided. The focus was on creating a sports car that rewarded driver skill while remaining accessible to enthusiasts.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not factory-backed like the Skyline GT-R, the S14 became the backbone of grassroots drifting and time attack racing. Its popularity in Formula Drift and amateur motorsport has cemented its legend in enthusiast circles.
editorial.engine_character: The KA24DE delivers smooth, linear power with surprising torque for a naturally aspirated four-cylinder. It's willing to rev but really shines in the midrange, providing the kind of predictable power delivery that builds driver confidence.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 5-speed manual offers precise, mechanical shifts with satisfying engagement. The throws are appropriately short and the clutch pedal provides good feedback, making it easy to execute smooth heel-toe downshifts.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The S14's chassis strikes an excellent balance between compliance and control. It's stiff enough to handle spirited driving but compliant enough for daily use, with neutral handling that can be adjusted to slight oversteer with throttle application.
editorial.steering_feel: The steering is direct and communicative, offering good feedback about what the front wheels are doing. Weight build-up is progressive and natural, giving drivers confidence to push harder into corners.
editorial.brake_confidence: The brakes provide adequate stopping power for the car's weight, with good pedal feel and reasonable fade resistance. While not exceptional, they're more than capable for spirited street driving and light track use.
editorial.sound_signature: The KA24DE produces a distinctive four-cylinder growl that's more refined than harsh. With an aftermarket exhaust, it develops a purposeful note that's loud enough to sound serious but civilized enough for daily driving.
editorial.ideal_owner: Perfect for the enthusiast who wants a proper rear-wheel-drive sports car with modification potential and the maturity to serve as both weekend toy and daily driver.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Those seeking immediate high performance, luxury appointments, or anyone unwilling to deal with the maintenance needs of a 25-30 year old sports car.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for examples with maintained suspension components and minimal rust, as both are expensive to address. The S14 is increasingly collectible, so buy the best example you can afford and preserve its sporting character.

expertReviews.verdict: This heavily modified S14 240SX delivers incredible thrills with 600whp from its SR20DET engine, but requires staying in the power band to shine. The kouki conversion and quality upgrades make it a stunning example, though parts availability and turbo lag are concerns. A true enthusiast's car that provides visceral driving experiences.

expertReviews.verdict: The S14 can be an amazing project car if you have money and experience, but it's one of the worst choices for broke high school kids or first-time buyers. The cars available to budget buyers have typically been neglected and need extensive work. Best suited for those with financial stability, a daily driver already, and mechanical knowledge.
